Texas Instruments Incorporated Introduces Industry's Smallest Power Management ICs For Solid State Drives
Tuesday, 13 Dec 2011 08:00am EST
Texas Instruments Incorporated announced that it has introduced a family of tiny, single-chip, power management integrated circuits (PMICs) for powering all the supply rails in solid state drives (SSDs), hybrid drives and other Flash memory management applications. The new LM10504, LM10503 and LM10506 PMICs improve reliability and reduce system cost and development time. Additional features include a power-saving deep sleep mode, built-in current limit and thermal protection, and power-down data protection.Â 
